    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1874-05-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1874-05-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="307" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d307">
                <head>No. 305.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Moran</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1874-05-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 30, 1874</date>.
                            (Received June 12.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 504.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: For the future use of the Department I have
                        the honor to send herewith a copy of the London Gazette of last evening, May
                        29, 1874, containing an official notice that the blockade of the Gold Coast,
                        established December 15, 1873, was raised on the 17th of April, 1874.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>BENJAMIN MORAN.</signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Board
                                        of Trade</hi>, (<hi rend="smallcaps">Harbor
                                        Department</hi>,)<lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Whitehall
                                        Gardens</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1874-05-28">
                                <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 28,
                                1874</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p rend="center">[From the London Gazette of May 29, 1874.]</p>
                    <p>The board of trade have received through the secretary of state for the
                            colonies a dispatch from the officer administering the government of the
                            Gold Coast, inclosing an official notice announcing that the blockade of
                            the Gold Coast, established December 15, 1873, was raised on the 17th of
                            April, 1874.</p>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
